input | kx '+\x' '#x'

each row is split at whitespace to x, row number is i:
 x:("col0";"col1";..)

each argument is evaluated per line and joined by space

unitype conversion for complete line
 xi short for `i$x
 xf           `f$x
 xs            `$x

convert individual fields
 0i short for  `i x 0
 2f            `f x 2
 3s            `s x 3

filter
 /condition/prog

aggregate
 sum+:x   (global assignment does not reassign each line)

examples
 number lines:                kx i x
 row sum:                     kx +/xf
 number of columns:           kx '#x'
 amplitude angle as cmplx     kx 0f@1f
 lines with first col peter   kx '/`peter~0s/x'
 column sum                   kx 'sum+:x' -e sum
